Question: **How did you find participating in this experiment? Please tell us anything you'd like to share about your experience.**
Response:
It was nice to get into a flow state with my music playing. I also have a different song stuck in my head at the moment. I felt aware of clenching my jaw and at so picked up a pen to hold and press the edges to get a different kind of sensory feedback (jaw clenching / teeth grinding causes damage to teeth). 
I am on concerta which I took in the morning as usual, so that is probably affecting my concentration levels positively, alongside being on day 1 of my period which will probably be adversely affecting my concentration levels / medication efficacy. 
I found it jarring if I missed a number or had to wait too long "doing nothing" whilst there was a transition from the no. 3.
